stem-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/lifecycle.py:\n  Line 5: * ``POST /admin/lifecycle/fanout/<action>`` — cron-fired entry point.\n\n  Line 10:   Body ``{\"org_id\": \"...\"}``. Same downstream code path as the fanout\n\n  Line 13: Auth: admin-key only (``auth.enforce_admin``). The fanout route is\n\n  Line 42: from core_api.services.lifecycle_audit import audit_begin, resolve_publisher_kwargs\n\n  Line 66: # fanout loop. Each pair = 1 HTTP POST to core-storage-api + 1 Pub/Sub\n\n  Line 70: # enough that the storage-writer pool is never saturated by fanout\n\n  Line 76:     \"\"\"Discovery query for the fanout — purge is the odd action here:\n\n  Line 117:     ``retention_days`` for purge). The publisher's Pydantic payload\n\n  Line 138: @router.post(\"/admin/lifecycle/fanout/{action}\")\n\n  Line 139: async def fanout_lifecycle_action(\n\n  Line 187:                 \"lifecycle fanout: failed to trigger one org; continuing\",\n\n  Line 196:         \"lifecycle fanout dispatched\",\n\n  Line 216:     downstream as the fanout-loop body. ``triggered_by`` records who\n\n  Line 248:     # body keys (dry-running a different ``retention_days`` without\n\n  Line 254:     body_retention = body.get(\"retention_days\")\n\n  Line 257:         # publishers don't accept ``retention_days``, so an unfiltered\n\n  Line 266:                 detail=\"'retention_days' is only valid for the 'purge-soft-deleted' action\",\n\n  Line 269:         # of ``{\"retention_days\": true}`` is rejected loudly.\n\n  Line 273:                 detail=\"'retention_days' must be an integer when provided\",\n\n  Line 283:                     f\"'retention_days' must be in [{MEMORY_RETENTION_MIN_DAYS}, {MEMORY_RETENTION_MAX_DAYS}]\"\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 210 matches (110 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":210,"truncated":true},"title":"fanout|lifecycle_audit|create_lifecyc